<p style="font-family:Fantasy; font-size:30px;">Adverbs</p>
<p>We can use adverbs to describe how somebody does something.</p>

<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>I speak English <b>well</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>He plays hockey <b>badly</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>We try to do our homework <b>correctly</b>.</i></p>

<p style="font-family:Courier;color:red;font-size:20px;">How to use them</p>
<p>To make adverbs, we normally add ly to the adjective. Sometimes the spelling is different.</p>

<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>She ran quick<b>ly</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>They sang beautiful<b>ly</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>The children are playing happi<b>ly</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>I dance terrib<b>ly</b>.</i></p>

<p>Some adverbs don't have ly.</p>

<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>I don't write English <b>well</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>My mum drives <b>fast</b>.</i></p>
<p style="font-family:Comic Sans MS"><i>Do you work <b>hard</b>?</i></p>


